Usage: vehicle check (-s|--specification FILE) [-t|--typeSystem ARG]

  Type-check a .vcl specification file.

Available options:
  -s,--specification FILE  The .vcl file containing the specification.
  -t,--typeSystem ARG      Which typing system should be used. i) Standard -
                           check whether the types written in the specification
                           are consistent. ii) Polarity - check whether
                           alternating quantifiers are used in the
                           specification. iii) Linearity - check whether
                           quantified variables are used linearly in the
                           specification.
  -h,--help                Show this help text
